quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  21,45,"Say: \"I warn you only on the strength of the Revelation (in which there is no doubt). But the deaf do not hear the call, however much they are warned"
  21,46,"And yet, if but a breath of your Lord’s punishment touches them, they are sure to cry: \"Oh, woe to us! We were indeed wrongdoers"
  21,47,"We will set up balances of absolute justice on the Day of Resurrection, and no person will be wronged in the least. Even though it be a deed so much as the weight of a grain of mustard seed, We will bring it forth to be weighed. We suffice as reckoners"
  21,48,"We granted Moses and Aaron the Criterion (the Book distinguishing between truth and falsehood,) and made it a (guiding) light and reminder for the God-revering, pious"
  21,49,"They stand in great awe of their Lord though unseen (and beyond their perception), and tremble with the thought of the Last Hour"
  21,50,"And this one (the Qur’an), too, is a Reminder full of blessings which We are sending down. Will you then reject it"
  21,51,"Indeed We had, before this, granted Abraham discretion and his particular consciousness of truth, and We knew him very well (in all aspects of his character)"
  21,52,"He said to his father and people: \"What are these images to which you pay such sincere devotion"
  21,53,"They said: \"We have found our forefathers worshipping them"
  21,54,"So, it is certain that,\" said he, \"both of you, you and your forefathers, have been in obvious error"
  21,55,"They asked: \"Is it the truth that you are proclaiming to us or are you jesting"
  21,56,"He answered: \"No, but your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, Who has originated them, each with particular features, and I am one to bear witness to this truth"
  21,57,"And (he made a decision:) \"By God, I will most certainly devise a plan against your idols as soon as you have turned your backs and gone away"